1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:02,120
♪

2
00:00:02,150 --> 00:00:03,650
( Shigechi gasping )

3
00:00:07,390 --> 00:00:09,560
Kira: This is deadly queen.

4
00:00:09,590 --> 00:00:12,430
i bestowed it
with the moniker myself.

5
00:00:12,460 --> 00:00:16,100
Hmm. I’m only telling you
because you’re going to die.

6
00:00:16,130 --> 00:00:18,800
After you bite the dust,
i’ll be able to sleep soundly.

7
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:22,670
Shigechi: Hey, didn’t I warn you
not to make a move against me?

8
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:24,770
You’re about to learn
that I mean business!

9
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:27,240
Deadly queen: Shibo!

10
00:00:29,580 --> 00:00:31,410
Kira: Well, now,
color me surprised.

11
00:00:31,450 --> 00:00:33,250
i crushed
several of these vermin,

12
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:35,750
yet you remain
completely unscathed.

13
00:00:35,790 --> 00:00:37,490
Shigechi: This is
your last chance, pal.

14
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:38,760
Move again, and i’ll slice

15
00:00:38,790 --> 00:00:41,320
whatever that big artery is
in your neck.

16
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:43,760
Oh, yeah, now I remember.
It’s called the carotid artery.

17
00:00:43,790 --> 00:00:45,460
You move a muscle,

18
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,260
and i’ll have my invincible
harvest hack it to pieces!

19
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:50,330
Judging by the look
of that stand of yours,

20
00:00:50,370 --> 00:00:52,100
it packs a wallop
if you’re up close,

21
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,340
but it’s really shitty

22
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:55,100
when it comes down
to long-range fighting.

23
00:00:55,140 --> 00:00:57,270
If I had to guess,
i’d say it’s got a range

24
00:00:57,310 --> 00:00:58,480
of one, maybe two meters.

25
00:00:58,510 --> 00:01:00,540
So go ahead, and make your move,

26
00:01:00,580 --> 00:01:03,110
if you’re ready to die,
that is. ( Chuckles )

27
00:01:03,150 --> 00:01:05,820
Kira: Fascinating.
From the looks of things,

28
00:01:05,850 --> 00:01:09,490
it seems each user is endowed
with a unique ability. Hmm.

29
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:13,890
"Stand." I believe
that’s the term you used.

30
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:17,490
i should tell you,
as far as special abilities go,

31
00:01:17,530 --> 00:01:21,360
deadly queen has one
that puts others to shame.

32
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,330
shigechi: Hmm?
What’s that in its hand?

33
00:01:23,370 --> 00:01:25,570
Grab it, harvest!

34
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,800
That’s weird.

35
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:29,640
It’s just a normal 100 yen coin.

36
00:01:29,670 --> 00:01:31,670
What the heck were you
planning to do with this?

37
00:01:31,710 --> 00:01:33,880
kira: Simple.
I was going to reveal

38
00:01:33,910 --> 00:01:37,250
what makes deadly queen such
a unique and terrifying stand.

39
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,350
there’s no point
in keeping its power secret

40
00:01:39,380 --> 00:01:41,680
when you’re already
as good as dead.

41
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:44,390
deadly queen
has an astonishing power.

42
00:01:44,420 --> 00:01:46,260
Any object that it touches

43
00:01:46,290 --> 00:01:49,760
becomes an explosive
that rips its target asunder.

44
00:01:49,790 --> 00:01:52,360
- ( Shigechi gasps )
- Kira: That’s right. Heh heh.

45
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:55,330
Even something as simple
as a 100 yen coin.

46
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,930
( Shigechi gasps )
Quick, harvest!

47
00:01:57,970 --> 00:02:00,870
You have to let go
of the coin right now!

48
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:03,810
( Screams )

49
00:02:07,910 --> 00:02:09,410
Kira: Hmm.

50
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:12,620
That didn’t take long.

51
00:02:12,650 --> 00:02:15,890
now a night
of glorious sleep awaits.

52
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,850
♪

53
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:25,330
( Singing in Japanese )

54
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,890
( School bell tolling )

55
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,330
Girl: Have you heard
about the beauty clinic

56
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,830
that helps you
find your true love?

57
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,260
Girl #2: Seriously?

58
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:01,760
don’t tell me
you actually believe that.

59
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,500
Girl #1: It worked
for this other girl.

60
00:03:03,530 --> 00:03:04,870
- ( Shigechi grunting )
- ( Kira gasps )

61
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:07,940
seems one blast
wasn’t enough to finish you.

62
00:03:07,970 --> 00:03:09,410
( Shigechi gasps )

63
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,710
What the hell?
What’d he do to me?

64
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:13,940
Wait a second. My face is...

65
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:15,350
( Squish )

66
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:18,950
( Gasping )

67
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:21,550
( Shrieks )
What happened to me?!

68
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:24,590
kira: I told you.
Deadly queen has the ability

69
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:27,490
to transform anything
it touches into a bomb.

70
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,730
That’s what it was doing

71
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:30,890
when you asked
about this 100 yen coin.

72
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:33,500
I press the detonator
whenever the urge hits me,

73
00:03:33,530 --> 00:03:35,030
and once it’s triggered,
my victim

74
00:03:35,060 --> 00:03:37,470
is blown to smithereens
from the inside out.

75
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,800
Though, in your case, shigechi,

76
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:43,470
it appears the blast partially
imploded your malformed face,

77
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:46,280
leaving behind
a stomach-churning cocktail

78
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:48,880
of facial fascia
and cerebral tissue.

79
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:52,550
Before I deliver the blow
that ends your wretched life,

80
00:03:52,580 --> 00:03:55,550
there’s something of great
importance I must ask you.

81
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:58,490
Earlier, you referred
to this power as a stand.

82
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,690
Do the others,
josuke and okuyasu,

83
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,490
also wield
the power of the stand?

84
00:04:02,530 --> 00:04:04,030
Shigechi: I don’t
wanna die here.

85
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:06,300
- Somebody help me, please.
- Kira: Oh, no, no.

86
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:08,300
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

87
00:04:08,330 --> 00:04:10,570
Your death is a necessity
at this point.

88
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:13,600
Now that you know my secret,
I can’t let you live.

89
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:17,040
It’s nothing personal, but I
can’t allow a single living soul

90
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:19,710
to know the true nature
of yoshikage Kira.

91
00:04:19,740 --> 00:04:21,410
Though, I must admit

92
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:24,750
I find myself fascinated
by these stand users.

93
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:27,550
I could figure this out
on my own, but i’d rather use

94
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:29,620
the fleeting resource
that lies before me.

95
00:04:29,650 --> 00:04:32,020
Josuke, okuyasu,

96
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:34,790
who are the others
besides them?

97
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:38,030
how many users
are residing in this town?

98
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:40,560
- ( Shigechi gasping )
- What are their powers?

99
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,100
Shigechi: Don’t know.
Just let me go, please.

100
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:45,500
Kira: Come now.
I’m sure you know more

101
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:48,810
than you’re letting on,
and if you refuse to tell me,

102
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:52,610
your parents will pay for it
with their lives.

103
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,410
Shigechi: What?

104
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,750
No, you can’t.

105
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:59,680
I won’t let you hurt
my mommy and daddy!

106
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,420
Kira: Well, I won’t have to

107
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:04,120
if you hurry up and give me
the answers i’m looking for.

108
00:05:04,150 --> 00:05:05,550
Now quit your stalling.

109
00:05:05,590 --> 00:05:07,590
I need to slip away
before anyone sees me.

110
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:10,830
Just the names will do.
hop to it, boy.

111
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:12,360
Shigechi: Hang on.

112
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,430
Everyone says there was
a murderer in this town,

113
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:15,970
and they’re all
trying to track him down

114
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,400
before he kills again.

115
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:19,640
It’s all making sense now.

116
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:21,640
The killer they were
talking about is you!

117
00:05:21,670 --> 00:05:23,410
You messed-up son of a bitch!

118
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,010
You killed reimi sugimoto, too!

119
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:27,440
kira: What?!
How do you know that girl?

120
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:30,950
( Gasps ) The little shit
can still use his stand?

121
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:32,780
This isn’t good.

122
00:05:32,820 --> 00:05:34,120
Deadly queen!

123
00:05:34,150 --> 00:05:36,550
♪

124
00:05:37,650 --> 00:05:39,760
Kira: Eh...

125
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:42,430
That brat.

126
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:44,860
I was so close to killing him.

127
00:05:51,530 --> 00:05:52,800
( Shigechi groans )

128
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:55,740
i managed
to give him the slip.

129
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:58,880
Now I just have
to get to josuke.

130
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:01,740
Once I make it there,

131
00:06:01,780 --> 00:06:05,420
he can use
his shining diamond to fix me.

132
00:06:05,450 --> 00:06:09,090
There’s no way i’m gonna
sit back and die like this.

133
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:18,860
No matter what, i’ll protect
my mommy and my daddy.

134
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,830
i promise,
i’ll fight to keep them safe

135
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:23,700
from this hand-hoarding monster!

136
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:28,570
That horrible creep
is rotten to the core,

137
00:06:28,610 --> 00:06:30,970
and i’d rather die
than let him live

138
00:06:31,010 --> 00:06:34,080
in the same town
as my mommy and daddy!

139
00:06:37,580 --> 00:06:40,950
( Gasping )

140
00:06:40,980 --> 00:06:43,950
I have to find josuke.
( Coughs )

141
00:06:43,990 --> 00:06:47,490
If he heals me, I can save ’em.

142
00:06:48,730 --> 00:06:50,460
( Groans )

143
00:06:50,490 --> 00:06:52,100
Girl: Sorry about that.

144
00:06:52,130 --> 00:06:54,460
Girl #2: Hey, kid,
you’re not hurt, are you?

145
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,070
Shigechi: I have to find him.

146
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:59,570
Girl #2: Gee, I wonder what’s
the matter with the little guy.

147
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,800
Girl #1: I don’t know, but he
looks like a middle schooler.

148
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:06,140
girl #2: Oh, no.
Something’s wrong with him.

149
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:08,140
let’s see
if we can find a teacher.

150
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:10,950
girl #1: No, we should
leave him be. He’s kinda weird.

151
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:12,450
Girl #3: Come on.

152
00:07:17,690 --> 00:07:20,690
Shigechi: J-josuke!

153
00:07:23,690 --> 00:07:26,830
( Gasping )

154
00:07:26,860 --> 00:07:30,570
J-josuke! ( Laughs )

155
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,570
( Gasps )

156
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,840
♪

157
00:07:35,870 --> 00:07:37,210
Kira: I recall
you said something

158
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,980
about people looking for me.

159
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:41,080
does that mean
there’s someone else here

160
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:44,210
who knows the truth
about reimi sugimoto’s murder?

161
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:46,720
Even if there is,

162
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,920
they won’t be able
to track me down.

163
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:53,990
The fact remains, no one knows
yoshikage kira’s true colors.

164
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:56,130
It’s a secret you’ll
have to carry with you

165
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,690
all the way to the grave.

166
00:07:57,730 --> 00:07:59,830
( Shigechi panting ) No.

167
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:02,630
I’m gonna protect
mommy and daddy.

168
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Kira: Sorry, but deadly queen

169
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:09,710
has already left its Mark
on the doorknob.

170
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:11,840
( Shigechi gasping )

171
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:16,210
Josuk--

172
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:20,720
josuke: Eh? Hmm?

173
00:08:22,090 --> 00:08:25,020
Kira: Behold the genius
of my deadly queen.

174
00:08:25,050 --> 00:08:26,590
( Birds chirping )

175
00:08:26,620 --> 00:08:29,260
All evidence of my true self
has been destroyed.

176
00:08:29,290 --> 00:08:32,200
Josuke: Hey, did you hear
someone call my name just now?

177
00:08:32,230 --> 00:08:34,260
Okuyasu: Yeah, most definitely.

178
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:37,130
( Gasps ) Josuke,
you seein’ what i’m seein’?!

179
00:08:37,170 --> 00:08:38,800
Josuke: Eh?

180
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:46,680
Harvest: I got it.

181
00:08:46,710 --> 00:08:47,680
( Yelps )

182
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:48,740
( Both gasp )

183
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:50,210
Josuke: No! Shigechi?!

184
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,820
Okuyasu: Shigechi!

185
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,120
Hey, something’s
not right, josuke.

186
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:59,920
Harvest was limping around
and bleeding before it vanished,

187
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,290
but that’s not how a stand
usually disappears.

188
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:05,860
and why the heck would
only one of ’em come to see us?

189
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:06,830
( Josuke gasps )

190
00:09:11,370 --> 00:09:13,600
Josuke: Let’s head over
to the middle school.

191
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,300
We have to find
shigechi right now.

192
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:17,010
♪

193
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,010
Kira: Hmm?

194
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,880
What’s this?

195
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:22,950
Where could I have
possibly lost my button?

196
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:24,710
Well, it can’t be helped.

197
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:26,950
I just have to visit my tailor

198
00:09:26,980 --> 00:09:29,220
and hope he carries
the same kind.

199
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:31,020
♪

200
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:32,960
( Arnold howling )

201
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:34,260
( Reimi gasps )

202
00:09:34,290 --> 00:09:36,030
( Shigechi screams )

203
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:39,200
( Screaming )

204
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:47,370
Reimi: It can’t be. Not again.

205
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:52,880
that foul demon,
he’s taken another life.

206
00:09:52,910 --> 00:09:57,180
another victim
screams across the skies.

207
00:09:57,210 --> 00:10:00,820
Why does this keep happening?!

208
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:02,790
( Shigechi screaming )

209
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,890
( Josuke gasping )

210
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,990
- shigechi.
- ( Okuyasu gasps )

211
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:11,330
♪

212
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:24,240
reimi:
There’s no doubt about it.

213
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:26,880
- This boy has passed.
- ( All gasp )

214
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:29,450
Shigekiyo must have had
a run-in with the killer,

215
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,450
one that cost him his life.

216
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,320
The whole thing is sickening.

217
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:35,380
I know what you
must be thinking.

218
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:38,050
How did they meet,
and how was he murdered?

219
00:10:38,090 --> 00:10:39,390
But I have no idea.

220
00:10:39,420 --> 00:10:42,130
I’m positive it was his doing.

221
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:44,860
I’d recognize the handiwork
of that murderer anywhere.

222
00:10:44,890 --> 00:10:45,830
Trust me.

223
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,970
Josuke: We just
looked for shigechi,

224
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,400
but couldn’t
find him anywhere.

225
00:10:50,430 --> 00:10:52,470
i still don’t get
how this could have happened.

226
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,970
We only let him out of our sight
for five minutes.

227
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,270
His books and school supplies

228
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:59,080
are in the same place
he left them,

229
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:01,710
and his parents have filed
a missing-person report,

230
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:04,810
though I doubt anything useful
will turn up at this point.

231
00:11:04,850 --> 00:11:06,180
I have to wonder...

232
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:08,150
koichi: Wait.
What are you saying, josuke?

233
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:10,350
You don’t think a stand user
did this, do you?

234
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,920
( Both grunt )

235
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,820
josuke: You guys
couldn’t possibly know this,

236
00:11:13,860 --> 00:11:15,960
but shigechi’s stand
harvest was--

237
00:11:15,990 --> 00:11:19,000
well, in a word, the thing
was damn near invincible,

238
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:20,200
so what the hell?

239
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:22,470
This guy killed shigechi
in five minutes.

240
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:25,900
Then he hid his body off campus
without anyone noticing.

241
00:11:25,940 --> 00:11:28,100
joseph: Well,
there you have it, jotaro.

242
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:29,870
It’s pretty obvious
that we’re dealing

243
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,270
with a murderous stand user.

244
00:11:31,310 --> 00:11:34,380
We can’t just sit by
and watch like spectators.

245
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:37,750
Jotaro: Hey, josuke, you said
you found a button, right?

246
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:39,920
Josuke: Oh, yeah.
Harvest brought it to me

247
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:41,380
before falling to pieces.

248
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:43,990
Here you go.

249
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:46,920
jotaro: This is
shigechi’s dying message.

250
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,490
It’s very likely harvest
pulled it off the murderer.

251
00:11:49,530 --> 00:11:52,000
If so, we’ve been given
an important clue.

252
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:53,460
( Josuke gasps )

253
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:55,330
Jotaro: I’d like to investigate
this thing further.

254
00:11:55,370 --> 00:11:56,800
Mind if I keep it?

255
00:11:56,830 --> 00:11:58,500
Josuke: Be my guest,
but how much information

256
00:11:58,540 --> 00:12:00,800
can you really get from
some run-of-the-mill button?

257
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,070
Jotaro: More than you
would think.

258
00:12:02,110 --> 00:12:04,310
we might find
the brand of the clothes

259
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:06,140
or even the manufacturer.

260
00:12:06,180 --> 00:12:07,840
Koichi: Good idea.

261
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:10,880
Okuyasu: Hey, if we’re done
with this little meeting,

262
00:12:10,910 --> 00:12:13,450
- I think i’m gonna go home.
- ( Scattered sighs )

263
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:16,790
Okuyasu: Talking about all this
is putting me in a weird mood.

264
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:18,420
I’m really pissed.

265
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:20,990
Come on, dad. Let’s go.

266
00:12:22,190 --> 00:12:23,430
Koichi: What’s up with him?

267
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:25,060
This isn’t like him at all.

268
00:12:25,090 --> 00:12:27,260
josuke: Yeah,
but I know how he feels.

269
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:30,400
Shigechi may have come off
as an annoying, greedy bastard,

270
00:12:30,430 --> 00:12:33,140
but there was something
undeniably lovable about him.

271
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:36,440
I still haven’t wrapped my head
around the fact that he’s gone.

272
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:39,580
honestly,
i’m not sure how to feel.

273
00:12:39,610 --> 00:12:43,080
I don’t know whether to rage
at the world or cry my eyes out.

274
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:45,820
It’s one of the most irritating
things you can imagine.

275
00:12:45,850 --> 00:12:47,550
I’m sure he feels it, too,

276
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:50,850
but it’s probably
way worse for him.

277
00:12:50,890 --> 00:12:52,290
Okuyasu: Shit.

278
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,260
Yukako: How could
something so horrific

279
00:12:54,290 --> 00:12:56,290
be happening in morioh
right under my nose?

280
00:12:56,330 --> 00:12:58,200
Tonio: I’ll make sure
all my customers know

281
00:12:58,230 --> 00:13:00,200
to keep an eye out
for this madman.

282
00:13:00,230 --> 00:13:03,330
( Aya sighs ) I can’t imagine
he would pay me a visit,

283
00:13:03,370 --> 00:13:05,100
but i’ll take some precautions.

284
00:13:05,130 --> 00:13:06,840
hazamada:
Keep in mind stand users

285
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:09,170
have a nasty habit
of finding each other.

286
00:13:09,210 --> 00:13:12,380
that said,
I hope we never meet.

287
00:13:12,410 --> 00:13:16,110
Rohan: So the time has come
for us all to take action.

288
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:18,050
( Reimi sighs )

289
00:13:19,350 --> 00:13:22,050
♪

290
00:13:39,370 --> 00:13:41,300
♪

291
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:44,970
Kira: Hmm? That was
definitely josuke.

292
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:49,050
And okuyasu is with him.

293
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,110
Woman: You won’t
believe what happened.

294
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,550
- Kira: Hmm?
- Woman: So you remember

295
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:54,880
how it was my birthday
this past Friday?

296
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,050
Well, that guy i’m seeing
decided to give me a gift.

297
00:13:57,090 --> 00:13:58,920
i mean, if you
can even call it that.

298
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,460
It’s just a shitty ring.

299
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:03,190
woman #2: I wouldn’t be
caught dead wearing this thing.

300
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:05,060
Woman #1: I know, but for now,

301
00:14:05,090 --> 00:14:07,330
I have to be like,
"oh, my god, I love it."

302
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,900
Jeez, i’m only dating him,
’cause his dad owns some land.

303
00:14:09,930 --> 00:14:11,370
The guy’s a total hick.

304
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:14,240
Woman #2: I bet, if this crap
is the best he can afford.

305
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,470
How much did it cost?

306
00:14:15,510 --> 00:14:17,640
woman #1:
I’m guessing like 150,000.

307
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:20,640
If you want it, I bet you
could sell it at a pawnshop.

308
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:24,210
I can’t let my beautiful fingers
be sullied by such trash.

309
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:25,480
( Laughs )

310
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:28,280
kira: Her soul is
as grotesque as they come,

311
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,920
but her hands and face
are quite lovely.

312
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:35,190
I’d like to set her soul right
and show her a glorious time.

313
00:14:35,230 --> 00:14:36,990
Woman #1: Well,
i’ve gotta get going.

314
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:38,030
I’ll see you soon.

315
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,260
Woman #2: Okay, then. Later.

316
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:41,530
♪

317
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,130
( Sizzling )

318
00:14:44,170 --> 00:14:46,670
Kira: Time we went
our separate ways.

319
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:49,470
We had a good run,
but it’s over now.

320
00:14:58,380 --> 00:15:00,220
I, mori, mori

321
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:02,450
♪ morioh Cho radio

322
00:15:02,490 --> 00:15:04,550
♪ morioh Cho radio

323
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:06,390
announcer:
With love, morioh Cho.

324
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:10,160
Kai: Good morning, everyone,
and welcome to morioh radio.

325
00:15:10,190 --> 00:15:11,560
This is Kai harada,

326
00:15:11,590 --> 00:15:14,560
your easy-listenin’
disc jockey extraordinaire.

327
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:17,130
are you ready
for a magnificent week?

328
00:15:17,170 --> 00:15:19,200
It’s hard to believe there are
only three days...

329
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,700
Kira: Feel free to dig in.

330
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:22,170
Kai: ...It’s July,
you know what that means.

331
00:15:22,210 --> 00:15:23,770
Kira: Oh, I almost forgot.

332
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:26,680
I’m going to be out of the house
today running a few errands,

333
00:15:26,710 --> 00:15:28,540
so i’d like you
to stay put, okay?

334
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:30,180
Kai: ...Have fun summer plans.

335
00:15:30,210 --> 00:15:32,180
Kira: We’ll wine and dine
when I get back.

336
00:15:32,220 --> 00:15:33,780
How does that sound?

337
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:36,150
kai: ...Fresh jam
on this bright, sunny day,

338
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:38,120
so enjoy the ride.

339
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:39,290
♪

340
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,390
Girl: Thankfully they still had

341
00:15:40,420 --> 00:15:41,660
some of the Parisian
specials left.

342
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:43,660
Girl #2: We got here
in the Nick of time.

343
00:15:43,690 --> 00:15:45,360
Girl #3: Let’s head
over to yohei lake.

344
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,800
girl #1:
But asuka’s not here yet.

345
00:15:46,830 --> 00:15:48,660
- girl #3: Oh, yeah.
- Koichi: It’s been four days

346
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:51,330
since we found out
about shigechi’s murder.

347
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:57,140
It’s been fairly quiet
since then, but...

348
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,240
There’s still a killer lurking

349
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:04,180
somewhere in the shadows
of this town.

350
00:16:04,210 --> 00:16:05,280
( Boy crying )

351
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,620
Koichi: When it
comes down to it,

352
00:16:06,650 --> 00:16:08,420
the mind only sees
what it wants to.

353
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:12,360
The look of guilt and innocence
is in the eye of the beholder.

354
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:18,760
( Gasps )

355
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,700
♪

356
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:24,770
Oh, uh, hi there, Mr. Jotaro.

357
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:28,470
Did anything weird stick out to
you during your investigation?

358
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,510
- jotaro: Hmm?
- Koichi: You remember, right?

359
00:16:30,540 --> 00:16:32,780
you said something about
examining the murderer’s button.

360
00:16:32,810 --> 00:16:35,310
Jotaro: Oh, that. Not yet.

361
00:16:35,350 --> 00:16:37,780
Hopefully that changes soon.

362
00:16:37,810 --> 00:16:40,250
koichi: Yeah,
it’d be a great help.

363
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:48,260
So, um, you headed
anywhere in particular?

364
00:16:48,290 --> 00:16:52,160
Jotaro: Hmm? No, not really.

365
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,900
I’m just walking.

366
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:55,400
Koichi: Oh, I see.

367
00:16:57,900 --> 00:16:59,800
( Thinking ) Son of a bitch.

368
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,540
Getting the strong,
silent type to chat

369
00:17:01,570 --> 00:17:02,810
is like pulling teeth.

370
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:05,740
Rohan-sensei’s pushiness
is unsettling,

371
00:17:05,780 --> 00:17:08,440
but jotaro’s silence
sends me into a panic.

372
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:11,280
There’s gotta be something
we can talk about.

373
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:12,620
Let’s see.

374
00:17:12,650 --> 00:17:15,820
I think that coat
of yours is badass!

375
00:17:15,850 --> 00:17:17,620
( Gasps )

376
00:17:17,650 --> 00:17:20,590
Jotaro: Looks like
we’ve found a shoe store.

377
00:17:20,620 --> 00:17:24,660
Koichi: Huh? What do you know?
It is a shoe store. Good catch.

378
00:17:24,690 --> 00:17:26,160
Uh, is something wrong?

379
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:29,470
Oh. It is a shoe store,

380
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,330
but they also
do simple alterations.

381
00:17:31,370 --> 00:17:32,770
well, that’s
certainly convenient.

382
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,600
If anyone ever needs
their skirt waists

383
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,610
and pants hemmed
I know where to send them.

384
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,840
Plus the electronics shop
sells flowers.

385
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,910
What made you wanna stop here?

386
00:17:40,940 --> 00:17:42,510
Jotaro: I did a bit of digging

387
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:44,380
and learned all about
the tailors of morioh,

388
00:17:44,410 --> 00:17:46,250
but it didn’t occur
to me ’til now

389
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,650
to ask about places like this.

390
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,690
Koichi: Oh!

391
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,520
Shopkeeper: Oh.

392
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:53,790
( Sips )

393
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:57,360
So is there something wrong
with the button?

394
00:17:57,390 --> 00:18:00,930
Jotaro: No. If it doesn’t
ring a bell, forget it.

395
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:04,670
I just couldn’t remember what it
was originally attached to.

396
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,370
Shopkeeper: That’s too bad.

397
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,370
hey, kid,
want an animal cracker?

398
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,370
I got plenty.

399
00:18:09,410 --> 00:18:11,570
I save the camels for last,

400
00:18:11,610 --> 00:18:12,880
but everything else
is fair game,

401
00:18:12,910 --> 00:18:15,280
so feel free to take
as many as you can eat.

402
00:18:15,310 --> 00:18:17,380
Koichi: Thanks, but, no,
i’m fine for now, sir.

403
00:18:17,410 --> 00:18:18,980
Shopkeeper: Suit yourself.

404
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:22,390
Getting back to the point,
not only have I seen it.

405
00:18:22,420 --> 00:18:25,290
Believe it or not, I actually
just finished some alterations

406
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:27,420
on the jacket
that it belongs to.

407
00:18:27,460 --> 00:18:28,890
A customer dropped by yesterday

408
00:18:28,930 --> 00:18:30,760
and asked me to replace
a missing button

409
00:18:30,790 --> 00:18:32,530
with the same kind
you brought in.

410
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,000
See for yourselves.

411
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:36,000
They’re identical.

412
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:37,400
Koichi: Does this mean...

413
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:38,870
Jotaro: It looks that way.

414
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,400
We’ve found it, koichi.

415
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,740
shopkeeper:
Found what, exactly?

416
00:18:41,770 --> 00:18:43,310
Koichi: Oh, uh, nothing.

417
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:45,740
More importantly, what did
the customer look like?

418
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:47,410
Do you recall his name?

419
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,650
Shopkeeper: Are you serious?
Of course I do.

420
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:52,350
What kind of businessman
would I be if I didn’t?

421
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:54,380
Each and every one
of my customers’s names

422
00:18:54,420 --> 00:18:56,550
is filed away
in the ol’ noggin here.

423
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:59,690
Anything less would just be rude
to my well-paying clientele.

424
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:02,590
I’ve got thousands of names
locked away in here.

425
00:19:02,630 --> 00:19:04,060
- Jotaro: You don’t say?
- Shopkeeper: Huh?

426
00:19:04,090 --> 00:19:06,360
Koichi: You’re absolutely
incredible, sir!

427
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,300
Would you mind telling us
who owns that jacket?

428
00:19:09,330 --> 00:19:10,770
Shopkeeper: Well...

429
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:13,340
I guess helping you out
couldn’t hurt nothin’.

430
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:15,610
I keep the names
on the order tags.

431
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:18,340
so you know,
I don’t need these tags.

432
00:19:18,370 --> 00:19:20,010
I remember the names just fine.

433
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,080
But things tend
to run more smoothly

434
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:23,550
when I have ’em on hand.

435
00:19:27,120 --> 00:19:28,680
( Koichi gasps )

436
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,350
Shopkeeper: Let’s see here.

437
00:19:30,390 --> 00:19:32,720
Huh, that’s interesting.

438
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,590
How do you read this last name?

439
00:19:34,620 --> 00:19:35,830
It has to be...

440
00:19:35,860 --> 00:19:37,530
Koichi: I don’t mean
to rush you, sir,

441
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:39,400
but maybe I can
help you figure it out.

442
00:19:39,430 --> 00:19:41,330
Shopkeeper: That can’t be it.

443
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:43,400
Maybe it’s...

444
00:19:43,430 --> 00:19:45,370
♪

445
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,040
( Gasping )

446
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:57,310
( Clanking )

447
00:20:00,150 --> 00:20:01,750
Stand: Look over here.

448
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:02,950
( Koichi gasps )

449
00:20:02,990 --> 00:20:04,790
shopkeeper:
Why’d my hand explode?

450
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:06,420
What the hell’s going on here?!

451
00:20:06,460 --> 00:20:08,730
Stand: Look over here.

452
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:11,060
( Koichi gasps ) Jotaro!
Tell me you’re seeing this!

453
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:12,600
Jotaro: Just keep
your guard up, koichi,

454
00:20:12,630 --> 00:20:13,930
and don’t get
any closer to it.

455
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:16,370
Stand: Hey, didn’t you hear me?

456
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,530
I said, "look over here."

457
00:20:18,570 --> 00:20:20,900
( Shopkeeper gasping )

458
00:20:20,940 --> 00:20:22,870
( Clanking )

459
00:20:24,570 --> 00:20:26,610
♪

460
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,610
( Koichi screams )

461
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,580
( Gasps )

462
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:31,550
Jotaro: Is that his stand?

463
00:20:34,450 --> 00:20:35,420
( Koichi gasps )

464
00:20:35,450 --> 00:20:37,520
Jotaro, look at the coat rack!

465
00:20:37,550 --> 00:20:39,760
Th-the killer is here,

466
00:20:39,790 --> 00:20:41,920
and he’s trying
to take the jacket!

467
00:20:43,490 --> 00:20:46,130
Kira: I never imagined
someone would go so far

468
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:48,870
as to investigate the button
that fell off my jacket.

469
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,530
What a careless mistake.

470
00:20:50,570 --> 00:20:51,840
This is bad.

471
00:20:51,870 --> 00:20:54,670
Have those two
already seen my name?

472
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:58,010
Why have I been faced with
nothing but adversity lately?

473
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,610
Jotaro: Ah, good grief.

474
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:02,710
This would be when he
comes to get his suit.

475
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:04,810
Kira: Panicking
would be a mistake.

476
00:21:04,850 --> 00:21:08,520
I’ll simply execute them with
deadly queen’s bomb type two,

477
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:10,890
just like
that pathetic punk, shigechi.

478
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:11,890
( Clanking )

479
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:12,990
( Both gasp )

480
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:14,720
Koichi: It’s moving again!

481
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:16,490
( Gasps ) Our evidence!

482
00:21:16,530 --> 00:21:17,960
Jotaro: Wait!

483
00:21:17,990 --> 00:21:20,200
We can’t go blindly after it.

484
00:21:20,230 --> 00:21:22,530
look at the way
he’s pulling the jacket.

485
00:21:22,570 --> 00:21:23,930
It’s strange.

486
00:21:23,970 --> 00:21:25,900
( Clanking )

487
00:21:26,970 --> 00:21:27,940
( Clicks )

488
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:29,740
( Ticking )

489
00:21:29,770 --> 00:21:31,540
( Kira shudders )

490
00:21:31,570 --> 00:21:34,540
Jotaro: What is his power?

